%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20report%2C%20Harlan%20Krumholz%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20medicine%20at%20Yale%20University%20who%20edits%20the%20Journal%20of%20the%20American%20College%20of%20Cardiology%20where%20the%20studies%20were%20published%2C%20said%20that%20the%20drug%20was%20%26quot%3Bsomehow%20quieting%20inflammation%2C%26quot%3B%20adding%20that%20the%20benefit%20was%20%26quot%3Bbroad%E2%80%A6%20there's%20not%20a%20group%20that%20doesn't%20seem%20to%20be%20benefiting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIs%20it%20a%20fountain%20of%20youth%E2%80%A6%20I%20would%20say%20if%20you're%20improving%20someone's%20cardiometabolic%20health%20substantially%2C%20then%20you%20are%20putting%20them%20in%20a%20position%20to%20live%20longer%20and%20better%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20just%20avoiding%20heart%20attacks.%20These%20are%20health%20promoters.%20It%20wouldn't%20surprise%20me%20that%20improving%20people's%20health%20this%20way%20actually%20slows%20down%20the%20ageing%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20also%20suggested%20that%20the%20drug%20could%20be%20used%20to%20treat%20a%20number%20of%20conditions%20linked%20to%20inflammation%2C%20including%20cancer%2C%20Alzheimer's%2C%20and%20Parkinson's%2C%20per%20The%20Times%20of%20London.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20studies%20were%20part%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.novonordisk.com%2Fnews-and-media%2Fnews-and-ir-materials%2Fnews-details.html%3Fid%3D166301%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESelect%20trial%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20tracked%2017%2C604%20adults%20aged%2045%20years%20or%20older%20for%20up%20to%20five%20years%20as%20they%20were%20given%20a%20once-weekly%20injection%20of%202.4%20mg%20of%20semaglutide%20or%20a%20placebo.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20participants%20were%20overweight%20or%20obese%20and%20had%20cardiovascular%20disease%20but%20no%20history%20of%20diabetes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20found%20that%20t