0in%20the%20months%20before%20that%2C%20he%20was%20telling%20people%20he%20might%20take%20his%20company%20public%2C%20and%20floated%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F8d6ceb0d-4cdb-4165-bdfa-4b95b3e07b2a%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2430%20billion%20valuation%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20his%20messaging%2Fsocial%20media%20company%2C%20which%20boasts%20more%20than%20900%20million%20users.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F242552a9-4280-46c0-9d61-bcf6ccd14400%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFinancial%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20says%20it%20has%20gotten%20a%20look%20at%20Telegram's%202023%20finances%2C%20and%20those%20numbers%20make%20it%20very%20hard%20to%20imagine%20the%20company%20could%20convince%20people%20it's%20worth%20anything%20like%20%2430%20billion%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20its%20founder%20and%20CEO%20wasn't%20looking%20at%20jail%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20big%20headline%20numbers%3A%20Last%20year%20Telegram%20lost%20%24108%20million%20on%20revenue%20of%20%24342%20million%2C%20according%20to%20the%20FT.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20uncommon%20for%20fast-growing%20consumer%20tech%20companies%20to%20be%20money%20losers%20when%20they%20go%20public.%20Twitter%20did%20that%20in%202012%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-reddit-loses-money-ipo-research-development-revenue-2024-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReddit%20did%20it%20this%20year%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bigger%20red%20flag%20for%20Telegram%20is%20the%20reported%20makeup%20of%20its%20business%3A%20While%20it%20makes%20a%20modest%20amount%20of%20money%20from%20conventional%20social%20media%20vectors%20%E2%80%94%20advertising%20and%20premium%20subscriptions%20%E2%80%94%20it%20makes%2040%25%20of%20its%20total%20from%20crypto%20services%2C%20the%20FT%20reports.%20It%20operates%20a%20digital%20%26quot%3Bwallet%26quot%3B%20where%20users%20can%20store%20crypto%20coins%20and%20the%20like%2C%20and%20it%20sells%20digital%20collectibles%2C%20like%20usernames%2C%20to%20its%20users.%20And%20that%20business%20seems%20to%20run%20primarily%20on%20Toncoin%2C%20a%20cryptocurrency%20originally%20built%20by%20Telegram.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20whole%20setup%2C%20as%20the%20FT%20notes%2C%20makes%20it%20seem%20like%20Telegram%20is%20%26quot%3Ba%20crypto%20firm%20with%20a%20sideline%20in%20messaging.%26quot%3B%20Telegram%20didn't%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20build%20a%20real%20business%20as%20a%20crypto%20trading%20hub%2C%20and%20that%20can%20be%20quite%20valuable%3A%20see%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffinance.yahoo.com%2Fquote%2FCOIN%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECoinbase%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20currently%20worth%20some%20%2445%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20asking%20investors%20to%20decide%20if%20Telegram%20is%20a%20social%20media%20company%20like%20Twitter%2C%20a%20messaging%20app%20like%20Whatsapp%2C%20or%E2%80%A6%20something%20else%2C%20fueled%20by%20a%20semi-obscure%20digital%20coin%2C%20would%20be%20a%20real%20ask.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20that's%20before%20you%20get%20to%20the%20issue%20of%20Durov's%20proposed%20valuation%2C%20and%20Telegram's%20very%20modest%20existing%20business%2C%20which%20don't%20sync%20up%20at%20all.%20Coinbase%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20eked%20out%20a%20small%20profit%20last%20year%20on%20revenues%20of%20%242.9%20billion.%20Twitter%2C%20prior%20to%20Elon%20Musk's%202022%20purchase%2C%20had%20been%20worth%20around%20%2425%20billion%2C%20and%20was%20doing%20around%20%245%20billion%20a%20year.%20Reddit%2C%20currently%20worth%20%2410%20billion%2C%20did%20%24800%20million%20last%20year.%20It's%20really%20hard%20to%20see%20how%20Telegram's%20%24342%20million%20stacks%20up%20to%20those.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPresumably%20any%20bankers%20working%20Telegram's%20theoretical%20IPO%20would%20play%20up%20the%20idea%20that%20while%20Telegram's%20top%20line%20is%20fairly%20modest%2C%20it%20is%20doing%20all%20of%20that%20with%20a%20teeny%20tiny%20staff%20of%20about%2050%20people.%20And%20that%20would%20give%20the%20company%20the%20ability%20to%20produce%20truly%20magnificent%20margins%2C%20one%20day%2C%20as%20the%20business%20matures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20will%20be%20a%20much%20harder%20sell%20after%20this%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpavel-durov-arrest-france-what-is-telegram-explained-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWhile%20we%20still%20don't%20fully%20understand%20the%20French%20case%20against%20Telegram%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20seems%20to%20center%20around%20the%20company's%20deliberate%20policy%20of%20doing%20almost%20zero%20moderation%2C%20and%20an%20alleged%20unwillingness%20to%20comply%20with%20government%20requests%20to%20fight%20illegal%20behavior%20on%20the%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDurov%20has%20said%20Telegram's%20no-moderation%2C%20no-compliance%20stance%20is%20a%20political%2Ftheological%20one.%20But%20it%20also%20has%20a%20real%20business%20component%3A%20As%20every%20big%20social%20network%20has%20learned%2C%20keeping%20an%20eye%20on%20what%20happens%20on%20your%20platform%2C%20and%20dealing%20with%20regulators%20who%20want%20a%20say%20about%20that%2C%20is%20a%20very%20expensive%20proposition%20that%20involves%20paying%20lots%20of%20humans.%20Right%20now%2C%20Durov%20doesn't%20have%20to%20worry%20about%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20Durov%20wants%20to%20placate%20the%20French%20government%20%E2%80%94%20and%20maybe%20others%20who%20are%20looking%20at%20similar%20charges%20%E2%80%94%20he%20may%20very%20well%20have%20to%20agree%20to%20change%20the%20way%20he%20runs%20his%20business%20and%20hire%20a%20lot%20more%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWho%20knows%3F%20Maybe%20that%20would%20make%20it%20more%20valuable%20in%20the%20long%20run.%20But%20it%20would%20definitely%20ding%20the%20company's%20P%26amp%3BL%20in%20the%20near-term.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20